  {
    "id": "erase-ed-two-keeps-cursor",
    "category": "erase",
    "spec_ref": "ECMA-48 §8.3.39 ED",
    "input": "\\e[10;30HDELME\\e[10;60H\\e[2J",
    "status": "supported",
    "expect": {
      "cursor": [
        10,
        60
      ],
      "absent": [
        "DELME"
      ]
    },
    "notes": "Positive guard for the ED-erase-in-place invariant (issue #29): ED 2 erases the whole display but, per ECMA-48 §8.3.39, must not move the active position. With the cursor parked at row 10 col 60, ESC[2J leaves it there rather than homing to (1,1). Fails against the old cursor-homing firmware and passes with the in-place erase; the absent DELME proves the erase actually ran."
  },
